# Create Domain Model

When creating a new domain model:

1. Place in `internal/domain/<context>/model/<entity>.go`
2. Use pure Go structs — no external dependencies
3. Add typed enums for status fields
4. Include `CreatedAt`, `UpdatedAt time.Time` fields
5. Use `uuid.UUID` for IDs (from `github.com/google/uuid`)

```go
package model

import (
    "time"
    "github.com/google/uuid"
)

type <Entity> struct {
    ID        uuid.UUID
    // ... fields
    CreatedAt time.Time
    UpdatedAt time.Time
}

type <Entity>Status string

const (
    <Entity>StatusActive   <Entity>Status = "active"
    <Entity>StatusInactive <Entity>Status = "inactive"
)
```
